# DESCRIPTION
# Problem from Calculus, single variable, Hughes-Hallett et al., 4th ed.
# WeBWorK problem written by Aaron Wooton, <wootton@up.edu>
# ENDDESCRIPTION

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(-5, 0);
$b=random(0, 5);
$c=random(1, 5);
$d=random(2, 9);
$a1=-$a;
$slope1=($b-$d);
$slope2=($a-$c);
$ans = "(($b-$d)/($a-$c))*(x+$a1 ) +$b";


BEGIN_TEXT

Find the equation of the line that passes through the points 
\( ($a ,$b ) \) and \( ($c ,$d ) \).
$BR 
\(y=\)\{ans_rule( 60) \}

END_TEXT

ANS(function_cmp($ans));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The slope is \( ($b-$d)/($a-$c))=($slope1 /$slope2) \). Using the point 
\( ($a ,$b ) \), the equation of the line is 
\( y- $b=($slope1 /$slope2 )(x-$a) \) or \( y=($slope1 /$slope2 )(x-$a) +$b \).

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
